\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2.3}{\ignorespaces The $\lambda ^2$ dependence of scattering kernel size is shown by the solid line. This has been derived from measurements made at $\lambda > 17$\nobreakspace {}cm \cite {Bower_2006}. The dotted line shows the derived intrinsic source size which scales as $\lambda ^{1.44}$. This was derived from measurements in the wavelength range, 2\nobreakspace {}cm\nobreakspace {}$< \lambda < 1.3$\nobreakspace {}mm \citep {Doeleman_2008}. The red circles show major-axis observed sizes of Sgr\nobreakspace {}A$^\star $ and the green points show the derived intrinsic major-axis size. This plot was reproduced from \citet {Doeleman_2008}. \relax }}{44}{figure.caption.16}
